Peer evaluation involves students giving each other comments on their work. This may happen in a classroom, online course, or group activity. Peer evaluation helps students learn by examining their classmates' work. Students also learn critical thinking, communication, and collaboration. Peer evaluation may be done by assigning a mark, offering written criticism, having a face-to-face conversation, or utilizing technology like online tools. The procedure might be teacher-led or self-directed. Papers, presentations, projects, and examinations may be peer-assessed. Peer evaluation helps students learn and improve critical thinking, communication, and collaborative skills. It gives instructors numerous views on student learning and useful feedback. 